---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Timeline" description="A day-by-day chronicle of 1948 and its antecedents — from the Balfour Declaration of 1917 through the armistice agreements of 1949.">

  <section class="hero" style="padding: var(--space-3xl) 0;">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <h1 style="font-size: var(--text-5xl);">Timeline</h1>
      <p class="subhead">The key events that led to 1948 — and what followed. Every entry is sourced.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:42rem;margin:0 auto;">

      <div style="border-left:3px solid var(--amber);padding-left:var(--space-xl);">
        
        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">1897</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">First Zionist Congress</h3>
          <p>Theodor Herzl convenes the First Zionist Congress in Basel, Switzerland. The Congress declares that "Zionism seeks to establish a home for the Jewish people in Palestine secured under public law."</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">November 2, 1917</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">The Balfour Declaration</h3>
          <p>British Foreign Secretary Arthur Balfour issues a 67-word letter pledging British support for "the establishment in Palestine of a national home for the Jewish people." The "existing non-Jewish communities" — over 90% of the population — are not consulted.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">1922</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">The British Mandate Begins</h3>
          <p>The League of Nations grants Britain the Mandate for Palestine, formalizing the Balfour Declaration. Jewish immigration accelerates.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">1936–1939</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">The Great Arab Revolt</h3>
          <p>Palestinian Arabs stage a six-month general strike followed by three years of armed insurrection against British rule and increasing Zionist settlement. The revolt is crushed, leaving Palestinian leadership and society decimated.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">1942</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">The Biltmore Program</h3>
          <p>Zionist leaders meeting at the Biltmore Hotel in New York call for the establishment of a Jewish commonwealth in all of Palestine, abandoning earlier formulations that only sought a "national home."</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">February 14, 1947</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">Britain Refers Palestine to the UN</h3>
          <p>Exhausted by World War II and unable to reconcile its contradictory promises, Britain asks the United Nations to resolve the Palestine question.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">November 29, 1947</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">UN Resolution 181: The Partition Plan</h3>
          <p>The UN General Assembly votes 33–13 to partition Palestine into two states. The proposed Jewish state receives 56% of the land despite Jews representing 33% of the population and owning 7% of the land. Zionist leaders accept; the Arab Higher Committee rejects.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">December 1947 – March 1948</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">Civil War Begins</h3>
          <p>Fighting erupts across Palestine. Zionist militias (Haganah, Irgun, Lehi) and Arab forces clash. Civilians on both sides are targeted. Palestinian displacement begins.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">March 10, 1948</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">Plan Dalet Adopted</h3>
          <p>The Haganah adopts Plan Dalet — a military strategy that authorizes the destruction of hostile Arab villages and the expulsion of their inhabitants. The plan is executed systematically in the following months.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">April 9, 1948</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">Deir Yassin Massacre</h3>
          <p>Irgun and Lehi fighters attack the village of Deir Yassin near Jerusalem. Between 100 and 120 villagers — including women, children, and the elderly — are killed. News spreads rapidly and accelerates the Palestinian exodus.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">May 14, 1948</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">Declaration of the State of Israel</h3>
          <p>David Ben-Gurion declares the establishment of the State of Israel in Tel Aviv, hours before the British Mandate expires. Within 24 hours, armies from Egypt, Jordan, Syria, Lebanon, and Iraq invade.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">May 1948 – March 1949</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">The 1948 Arab-Israeli War</h3>
          <p>Israeli forces, unified under the IDF, fight Arab armies to a series of armistices. By war's end, Israel controls 78% of Mandatory Palestine — 22% more than the UN Partition Plan allocated. Jordan occupies the West Bank; Egypt holds Gaza.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">December 11, 1948</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">UN Resolution 194: Right of Return</h3>
          <p>The UN General Assembly adopts Resolution 194, affirming that "refugees wishing to return to their homes and live at peace with their neighbours should be permitted to do so." The resolution has been reaffirmed more than 130 times. Israel has never implemented it.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">By 1949</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">The Aftermath: The Nakba in Numbers</h3>
          <p>Between 700,000 and 750,000 Palestinians displaced. Between 400 and 600 villages destroyed or depopulated. A refugee crisis begins that continues to this day — with more than 5.9 million registered Palestinian refugees as of 2026.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">June 1967</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">The Six-Day War</h3>
          <p>Israel captures the West Bank, East Jerusalem, Gaza, Golan Heights, and Sinai. The occupation of Palestinian territories begins — now the longest military occupation in modern history.</p>
        </div>

        <div style="margin-bottom:var(--space-2xl);">
          <time style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:var(--text-sm);color:var(--amber);font-weight:600;">July 19, 2024</time>
          <h3 style="margin:var(--space-xs) 0 var(--space-sm);">ICJ Advisory Opinion</h3>
          <p>The International Court of Justice rules that Israel's continued presence in the occupied Palestinian territory is unlawful under international law, and that Israel is obligated to end the occupation "as rapidly as possible."</p>
        </div>

      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>
